==English==

===Pronunciation===
{{substub}}

===Etymology===
From [[Greek]] [[ηλιοκεντρικός]] (''heliokentrikos'') "having the sun as his centre", from [[Ancient Greek]] [[ήλιος]] (''helios'') "sun" + [[κέντρον]] (''kentron'') "centre".

===Noun===
''heliocentric''

# one who is obsessed with the sun and its movements and patterns

===Adjective===
''heliocentric''

# having to do with the obsession with the sun and its movements and patterns
# ''(astronomy)'' having the sun at the center; usually in reference to a [[solar system]]

====Antonyms====
*[[geocentric]]

